
// support for throwing/catching errors is based on two functions:
// 1. throw(e)
//      begin unwinding the process using e as the raised error
//      stop when the process is completely unwound or a try is encountered
// 2. try(f, g)
//      call f
//      if f causes the process to unwind:
//          call g with the raised error
//          return what g returns
//      otherwise return what f returns

